    Establishments

    Each establishment serves a distinct purpose and contributes to the community's general well-being. Residents must have access to these businesses in order to meet their daily requirements and develop a sense of community engagement. Furthermore, the presence of thriving businesses can help attract new residents and businesses to the area, thereby strengthening the community as a whole.

    Education

    Established Schools

    Cogorin Ibaba National High School

    Cogorin Ibaba Elementary School offers an educational experience that prepares and inspires students.

    Cogorin Ibaba Elementary School

    Cogorin Ibaba National High School provides a quality education that fosters the development of students on an academic, social and moral level. It offers an extensive curriculum in the sciences, mathematics and humanities, as well as an active student life.

    Multi Purpose Hall

    Multipurpose Hall is a one-stop shop for all barangay needs, offering a range of services to meet the needs of the community.

    Barangay Tanod HQ

    Barangay Tanod Headquarters strives to provide quality public service and safety, upholding the highest standards of accountability and professionalism.


    Community Chapel

    Community Chapel strives to create a sense of community and spiritual growth through Sunday services, Bible studies, and other activities.

    About Lopez

    the Municipality of Lopez (Tagalog: Bayan ng Lopez), is a 1st class municipality in the province of Quezon, Philippines. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 94,657 people
